6 An Act relating to medical marijuana; amending 63
O.S. 2021, Section 427.10, as amended by Section 12,
7 Chapter 251, O.S.L. 2022 (63 O.S. Supp. 2024, Section
427.10), which relates to physician recommendations;
8 updating statutory language; requiring creation and
maintenance of certain registry; providing certain
9 requirements for listing on registry; requiring
promulgation of certain rules; and declaring an
10 emergency.
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 63 O.S. 2021, Section 427.10, as
14 amended by Section 12, Chapter 251, O.S.L. 2022 (63 O.S. Supp. 2024,
15 Section 427.10), is amended to read as follows:
16 Section 427.10. A. Only licensed Oklahoma allopathic,
17 osteopathic and podiatric physicians may provide a medical marijuana
18 recommendation for a medical marijuana patient license under the
19 Oklahoma Medical Marijuana and Patient Protection Act.
20 B. A physician who has not completed his or her first residency
21 shall not meet the definition of “physician” under this section and
22 any recommendation for a medical marijuana patient license shall not
23 be processed by the Oklahoma Medical Marijuana Authority.
24
